##Requirements

## Functional Requirements
- [ ] Text feilds to input username, password and domain name
- [ ] Strength is displayed with visual indicator (e.g., Weak, Fair, Good, Strong, Very Strong)
- [ ] Color-coded feedback (red, orange, yellow, light green, dark green)
- [ ] Warning displayed if username is found in password
- [ ] Warning displayed if password is found in username
- [ ] Clear error message: "Password should not contain your username"
- [ ] Suggestions displayed in real-time as user types



## Non-Functional Requirements

### Security
- No passwords stored or logged
- All breach checks use k-anonymity
- HTTPS required for production
- Client-side hashing for breach checks

### Performance
- Initial load time < 2 seconds
- Password analysis < 100ms
- HIBP check < 2 seconds
- Support 1000 concurrent users




## Definition of Done
- [ ] All acceptance criteria met
- [ ] Unit tests written and passing (>80% coverage)
- [ ] Integration tests for HIBP API
- [ ] Accessibility audit passed (WCAG AA)
- [ ] Cross-browser testing completed
- [ ] Documentation written
- [ ] Security review completed
- [ ] Performance benchmarks met
- [ ] Deployed to staging environment
- [ ] User acceptance testing passed
